<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-657] Unable to invoke method on BuilderClassSupport subclasses</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-657</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A class that extends BuilderClassSupport and that is defined in a groovy script cannot invoke any method on itself in the createNode(...) methods because the method invokation will be intercepted. I don&apos;t know, how this could be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is highly desireable, though.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12812741">GROOVY-657</key>
            <summary>Unable to invoke method on BuilderClassSupport subclasses</summary>
