                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14460596" author="guillaume" created="Tue, 19 Oct 2004 15:23:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Philipp, that&apos;s the principle of BuilderSupport, all invokations go through the createNode() methods. It&apos;s not a limitation. If you want to call a method defined in your class extending BuilderSupport, you should check in createNode() that the method called is the one defined in your object, then delegate it yourself to your object&apos;s method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460651" author="llucifer" created="Tue, 19 Oct 2004 16:31:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Guillaume, I think I did not understand exactly how to achive what you suggested. I did create a BuilderClass that has a private method foo() which is I wanted to call from the diverse createNode(...) methods. But the method call on foo what &quot;routed&quot; through the createNode methods again. I did look into BuilderSupport and came to the conclusion that &lt;em&gt;every&lt;/em&gt; invocation on a method of the Builder is intercepted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps you can enlight me with a short example or better add an example to the groovy documentation. The existing example in the docs that logs the methods calls does not call methods on itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460637" author="guillaume" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2004 17:58:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Philipp, it&apos;s now possible to write your builders in Groovy and call normal methods, without createNode() always intercepting all method calls. I&apos;ve added a test case which shows that, it&apos;s in groovy-core/src/test/groovy/bug/InvokeNormalMethodFromBuilder_Bug657.&lt;br/&gt;
The fix was done thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-677&quot; title=&quot;Call statically typed method first before anything else&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-677&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-677&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I commited yesterday.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
